page.title: 06BENOVER VILLAGE
page.content: WE STARTED AT 'GROWIT NURSERIES'.THERE IS A NEW HOUSE ON THE RIGHT,AND ON THE LEFT A BIG HOP GARDEN. ON THE WAY WE PASSED A BIG HOUSE CALLED 'NORMANS' WHICH LOOKED VERY OLD.AT THE CROSSROADS THERE IS A POSTBOX. A BIT NEARER THE CROSSROADS THERE WERE TWO OLD HOUSES; ONE OF THEM USED TO BE AN OLD FARMHOUSE CALLED 'LITTLE BENOVER'. NEARBY IS A THATCHED HOUSE CALLED 'THATCHERS'. THE ROAD WE WERE WAITING BY WAS VERY BUSY. WE SAW SOME GRAZING LAND AND WE PASSED A PUB WHICH WAS CALLED 'THE WOOLPACK'(THIS PUB IS 400 YEARS OLD).IT WAS CALLED THE WOOLPACK BECAUSE THERE WERE A LOT OF SHEEP HERE.
